{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Fréchet Mean and Tangent PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "Lead author: Nina Miolane.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how to compute the Fréchet mean of a data set.\n",
    "Then it performs tangent PCA at the mean."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "INFO: Using numpy backend\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import geomstats.backend as gs\n",
    "import geomstats.visualization as visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "from geomstats.learning.frechet_mean import FrechetMean\n",
    "from geomstats.learning.pca import TangentPCA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## On the sphere"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate data on the sphere"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from geomstats.geometry.hypersphere import Hypersphere\n",
    "\n",
    "sphere = Hypersphere(dim=2)\n",
    "data = sphere.random_von_mises_fisher(kappa=15, n_samples=140)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(data, space=\"S2\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.7, label=\"Data points\")\n",
    "ax.set_box_aspect([1, 1, 1])\n",
    "ax.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Fréchet mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We compute the Fréchet mean of the simulated data points."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mean = FrechetMean(metric=sphere.metric)\n",
    "mean.fit(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "mean_estimate = mean.estimate_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(data, space=\"S2\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Data points\")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    mean_estimate, space=\"S2\", color=\"red\", ax=ax, s=200, label=\"Fréchet mean\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_box_aspect([1, 1, 1])\n",
    "ax.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Tangent PCA (at the Fréchet mean)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We perform tangent PCA at the Fréchet mean, with two principal components."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tpca = TangentPCA(metric=sphere.metric, n_components=2)\n",
    "tpca = tpca.fit(data, base_point=mean_estimate)\n",
    "tangent_projected_data = tpca.transform(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We compute the geodesics on the sphere corresponding to the two principal components."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "geodesic_0 = sphere.metric.geodesic(\n",
    "    initial_point=mean_estimate, initial_tangent_vec=tpca.components_[0]\n",
    ")\n",
    "geodesic_1 = sphere.metric.geodesic(\n",
    "    initial_point=mean_estimate, initial_tangent_vec=tpca.components_[1]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "n_steps = 100\n",
    "t = gs.linspace(-1.0, 1.0, n_steps)\n",
    "geodesic_points_0 = geodesic_0(t)\n",
    "geodesic_points_1 = geodesic_1(t)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n",
    "xticks = gs.arange(1, 2 + 1, 1)\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_ticks(xticks)\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Explained variance\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Number of Principal Components\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylim((0, 1))\n",
    "ax.bar(xticks, tpca.explained_variance_ratio_);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "nbsphinx-thumbnail"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    geodesic_points_0, ax, space=\"S2\", linewidth=2, label=\"First component\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    geodesic_points_1, ax, space=\"S2\", linewidth=2, label=\"Second component\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    data, ax, space=\"S2\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Data points\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    mean_estimate, ax, space=\"S2\", color=\"red\", s=200, label=\"Fréchet mean\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_box_aspect([1, 1, 1]);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## In the Hyperbolic plane"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate data on the hyperbolic plane"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from geomstats.geometry.hyperboloid import Hyperboloid\n",
    "\n",
    "hyperbolic_plane = Hyperboloid(dim=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "data = hyperbolic_plane.random_point(n_samples=140)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    data, space=\"H2_poincare_disk\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.7, label=\"Data points\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Fréchet mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We compute the Fréchet mean of the data points."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mean = FrechetMean(metric=hyperbolic_plane.metric)\n",
    "mean.fit(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "mean_estimate = mean.estimate_"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    data, space=\"H2_poincare_disk\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Data points\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    mean_estimate,\n",
    "    space=\"H2_poincare_disk\",\n",
    "    color=\"red\",\n",
    "    ax=ax,\n",
    "    s=200,\n",
    "    label=\"Fréchet mean\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Tangent PCA (at the Fréchet mean)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We perform tangent PCA at the Fréchet mean."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tpca = TangentPCA(metric=hyperbolic_plane.metric, n_components=2)\n",
    "tpca = tpca.fit(data, base_point=mean_estimate)\n",
    "tangent_projected_data = tpca.transform(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We compute the geodesics corresponding to the first components of the tangent PCA."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "geodesic_0 = hyperbolic_plane.metric.geodesic(\n",
    "    initial_point=mean_estimate, initial_tangent_vec=tpca.components_[0]\n",
    ")\n",
    "geodesic_1 = hyperbolic_plane.metric.geodesic(\n",
    "    initial_point=mean_estimate, initial_tangent_vec=tpca.components_[1]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "n_steps = 100\n",
    "t = gs.linspace(-1.0, 1.0, n_steps)\n",
    "geodesic_points_0 = geodesic_0(t)\n",
    "geodesic_points_1 = geodesic_1(t)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n",
    "xticks = gs.arange(1, 2 + 1, 1)\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_ticks(xticks)\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Explained variance\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Number of Principal Components\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylim((0, 1))\n",
    "ax.bar(xticks, tpca.explained_variance_ratio_);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(111)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    geodesic_points_0,\n",
    "    ax,\n",
    "    space=\"H2_poincare_disk\",\n",
    "    linewidth=2,\n",
    "    label=\"First component\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    geodesic_points_1,\n",
    "    ax,\n",
    "    space=\"H2_poincare_disk\",\n",
    "    linewidth=2,\n",
    "    label=\"Second component\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    data, ax, space=\"H2_poincare_disk\", color=\"black\", alpha=0.2, label=\"Data points\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax = visualization.plot(\n",
    "    mean_estimate,\n",
    "    ax,\n",
    "    space=\"H2_poincare_disk\",\n",
    "    color=\"red\",\n",
    "    s=200,\n",
    "    label=\"Fréchet mean\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.legend();"
   ]
  }
 ],
